= Project Context
<project-context>
== Purpose
<purpose>
The project aims to integrate Adversarial Autoencoders (AAE) with
machine learning methods to perform objective classification of
financial transactions. The goal represents a fraud detection system
that classifies transactions into three types: - Regular - Local Anomaly
\- Global Anomaly

The core approach involves training an AAE to generate latent vectors,
which are then used as features for supervised learning algorithms (SVM,
Random Forest, Naive Bayes) to improve classification performance
compared to using original features.

