== Project Conventions
<project-conventions>
=== Code Style
<code-style>
- #strong[Naming];: Mixed use of `camelCase` (e.g., `latentVecDim`,
  `datasetFile`) and `snake_case` (e.g., `seed_value`, `clf_name`).
  Class names use `PascalCase`.
- #strong[Formatting];: 4-space indentation.
- #strong[Comments];: Generous use of comments to denote interions (e.g.,
  `importing pytorch libraries`, `specify first layer`).

=== Architecture Patterns
<architecture-patterns>
- #strong[Modular Components];: Network components are separated into
  individual files (e.g., `Encoder.py`, `Decoder.py`,
  `Discriminator.py`).
- #strong[Experiment Workflow];:
  + #strong[Train];: `validation_v0.py` trains the autoencoder.
  + #strong[Generate];: `generateDatasets.py` creates latent datasets in
    `latent_data_sets/`.
  + #strong[Experiment];: `MAUC_Exp.py` (latent features) and
    `MAUC_rawExp.py` (original features) run classification experiments.
  + #strong[Results];: Outputs are saved to `results/`.

=== Directory Structure
<directory-structure>
- `data/`: Input datasets.
- `latent_data_sets/`: Generated latent vector datasets.
- `models/`: Saved model artifacts.
- `results/`: Experiment outputs (plots, text files).
- `openspec/`: Project specifications and agent instructions.

=== Testing Strategy
<testing-strategy>
- #strong[Ad-hoc Testing];: Testing appears to be done via specific test
  scripts (e.g., `test_gaussianmixplot.py`, `testingBarPlot.py`) rather
  than a comprehensive unit test suite.
- #strong[Validation];: `validation_v0.py` serves as the primary
  validation script for the autoencoder training.

== Domain Context
<domain-context>
- #strong[Fraud Detection];: The domain focuses on identifying anomalies
  in financial data.
- #strong[MAUC];: Metric Area Under the Curve, a key performance metric
  used in this project.
- #strong[Latent Space];: The compressed representation of data
  generated by the autoencoder, critical for feature engineering in this
  pipeline.

